<TITLE> Govt approves NCT </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 18 (bdnews24.com)  The government has given the green light for setting up a New-mooring Container Terminal (NCT) at the Chittagong port. The cabinet's purchase committee on Sunday approved the project worth Tk 97.85 crore. It also approved a Tk 57 crore project to build apartments for low and mid-income groups in the capital's Mohammadpur area. Approval for appointment of consultants also came from Sunday's meeting. PDP Australia Ltd was approved for the 'Spending Public Expenditure Management Programme' worth Tk 97.03 crore. Meanwhile, two food procurement projects were also approved. The committee approved purchase of 50,000 tonnes of non-basmati rice for Tk 171 crore and another Tk 457 crore was approved to buy 3 lakh tonnes of wheat. bdn
